}} 'Samuelson' is an English language patronymic surname meaning son of
[[Samuel]]. There are alternate spellings such as the Swedish Samuelsson and the
Scandinavian Samuelsen. It is uncommon as a given name. Samuelson may refer to:

* Sir Bernhard Samuelson (1820–1905), British industrialist and educationalist
* Cecil O. Samuelson (1941 – ), president of Brigham Young University, USA
* Don Samuelson (1913–2000), Republican politician from Idaho, USA
* Emily Samuelson (1990 - ), American ice dancer
* G. B. Samuelson (1888–1947), British filmmaker
* Godfrey Samuelson (1863–1941), British Liberal Party politician, Member Of
  Parliament 1887–1892
* Gar Samuelson (1958–1999), drummer for the band Megadeth
* Sir Henry Bernhard Samuelson (1845–1937), English Liberal Party politician
* Marcus Samuelsson (1970- ), Ethiopian restaurateur
* Martha Samuelson ( - ), US business consultant
* Mikael Samuelson (1951 – ), Swedish stage actor
* Pamela Samuelson, American, professor of law at the University of
  California, Berkeley
* Paul Samuelson (1915–2009), Nobel-Prize-winning American economist
* Peter Samuelson (1951 – ), American filmmaker, philanthropist
* Ralph Samuelson (1903–1977), inventor of water skiing
* Robert J. Samuelson, contributing editor for Newsweek and The Washington Post
* Sivert Samuelson (1883–1958), South African cricketer
* Sir Sydney Samuelson (1925 - ), British movie producer
* Victor Samuelson ( - ), businessman
